1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:50,154 --> 00:00:51,239
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

3
00:00:51,322 --> 00:00:52,574
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

4
00:00:52,657 --> 00:00:54,075
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,076
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

6
00:00:59,831 --> 00:01:02,876
No matter how beautiful and grand
their lives may have been,

7
00:01:03,918 --> 00:01:05,503
the dead tell no tales.

8
00:01:06,921 --> 00:01:08,464
Thus, murderers believe

9
00:01:08,548 --> 00:01:11,718
that they can keep
their crimes hidden for good.

10
00:01:21,352 --> 00:01:22,520
But the problem is,

11
00:01:22,604 --> 00:01:24,230
they're wrong.

12
00:01:25,356 --> 00:01:27,066
Some things do exist

13
00:01:27,150 --> 00:01:29,319
even if they're invisible.

14
00:01:30,612 --> 00:01:33,281
They're always around us.

15
00:01:34,282 --> 00:01:35,533
Actually…

16
00:01:36,576 --> 00:01:38,578
He came into the office…

17
00:01:38,661 --> 00:01:39,579
They're around me.

18
00:01:41,289 --> 00:01:42,123
And unexpectedly,

19
00:01:42,749 --> 00:01:44,584
they're talkative.

20
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:47,962
What about it? Hear me out, Mr. Attorney!

21
00:01:48,046 --> 00:01:50,673
Well, I understand why.

22
00:01:50,757 --> 00:01:53,051
- They have no power to take revenge.
- Tell them something!

23
00:01:53,134 --> 00:01:54,219
Nor do they know how.

24
00:01:57,013 --> 00:01:58,723
WITNESS STAND

25
00:02:03,895 --> 00:02:05,813
This is exactly why they need

26
00:02:05,897 --> 00:02:07,732
someone to hear their resentful stories

27
00:02:07,815 --> 00:02:09,692
and convict those who deserve punishment,
which is me,

28
00:02:10,276 --> 00:02:11,277
Shin I-rang.

29
00:02:11,861 --> 00:02:12,737
Your Honor.

30
00:02:13,988 --> 00:02:15,198
I have an objection.

31
00:02:20,370 --> 00:02:21,996
The culprit…

32
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,373
is someone else.

33
00:02:27,877 --> 00:02:28,878
However,

34
00:02:29,462 --> 00:02:32,215
I wasn't a ghost-seeing attorney
from the start.

35
00:02:33,841 --> 00:02:35,093
ONE YEAR AGO

36
00:02:35,176 --> 00:02:36,427
Attorney Shin I-rang.

37
00:02:36,511 --> 00:02:38,596
Why don't you tell us
about your strengths?

38
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,181
EPISODE 1

39
00:02:40,265 --> 00:02:42,100
I have two hearts.

40
00:02:42,183 --> 00:02:45,812
A strong heart that allows me
to race until I win a case,

41
00:02:45,895 --> 00:02:47,939
and a warm heart that motivates me

42
00:02:49,482 --> 00:02:50,858
to create a righteous society.

43
00:02:50,942 --> 00:02:53,820
INTERVIEW ADMISSION TICKET
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

44
00:03:03,788 --> 00:03:05,415
You can just walk away.

45
00:03:07,959 --> 00:03:10,503
I was meaning
to walk past you today anyway.

46
00:03:10,586 --> 00:03:11,587
That's good, then.

47
00:03:12,338 --> 00:03:13,214
Go on.

48
00:03:21,556 --> 00:03:22,640
It's okay. Just go on.

49
00:03:26,352 --> 00:03:29,230
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

50
00:03:52,837 --> 00:03:53,671
Hi, Mom.

51
00:03:54,339 --> 00:03:55,423
Hey.

52
00:03:56,799 --> 00:03:58,509
You must be tired from work today.

53
00:03:58,593 --> 00:03:59,719
Not at all.

54
00:04:00,595 --> 00:04:02,138
I do this because I like it.

55
00:04:03,765 --> 00:04:04,974
Oh, this?

56
00:04:05,558 --> 00:04:07,894
The vegetable lady was coughing.

57
00:04:07,977 --> 00:04:09,437
The flu is going around these days.

58
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,522
You're such a softie.

59
00:04:11,606 --> 00:04:14,442
Your older sister's shop
has tons of vegetables,

60
00:04:14,525 --> 00:04:15,651
and you bought extra.

61
00:04:15,735 --> 00:04:17,987
It's nice to have a lot of vegetables.

62
00:04:18,071 --> 00:04:20,490
Koreans eat too much meat. It's not good.

63
00:04:20,573 --> 00:04:22,867
Says someone whose mom is a butcher.

64
00:04:23,618 --> 00:04:25,286
What I'm trying to say is--

65
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:26,954
Shut it, and just bring this over.

66
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:31,709
Okay.

67
00:04:32,335 --> 00:04:34,128
Sir, don't get drunk like last time.

68
00:04:37,131 --> 00:04:39,050
- Please enjoy.
- Oh, thank you.

69
00:04:40,468 --> 00:04:42,887
Welcome back, my dear brother-in-law.

70
00:04:43,471 --> 00:04:45,390
Is it a periodic drama this time?

71
00:04:45,473 --> 00:04:47,558
I have as many as two lines for this role.

72
00:04:48,476 --> 00:04:49,936
Congratulations, my lord.

73
00:04:50,019 --> 00:04:51,938
Thank you.

74
00:04:52,021 --> 00:04:53,106
Honey.

75
00:04:53,189 --> 00:04:54,982
I'm on my way, my lady.

76
00:04:56,984 --> 00:04:59,529
Da-bong, your uncle is here.

77
00:05:01,447 --> 00:05:02,949
Put me down, Uncle.

78
00:05:03,032 --> 00:05:04,450
Look at you, brat.

79
00:05:04,534 --> 00:05:06,327
Choose between Carbot and me.

80
00:05:06,411 --> 00:05:08,454
I choose you. Happy now?

81
00:05:09,539 --> 00:05:10,832
Yes, happy.

82
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:15,294
Why are you here again?
I told you to stop coming.

83
00:05:15,378 --> 00:05:17,213
I might not be able to come for real soon.

84
00:05:17,296 --> 00:05:18,714
I want to help out while I can.

85
00:05:18,798 --> 00:05:19,966
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

86
00:05:20,049 --> 00:05:22,927
Oh, right. How was the interview?
How did it go?

87
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:25,054
Everyone seemed worried.

88
00:05:25,805 --> 00:05:27,765
Worried? Why?

89
00:05:27,849 --> 00:05:30,726
Isn't it obvious?
Words spread fast in this field.

90
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,311
They were worried they might lose me.

91
00:05:32,395 --> 00:05:34,272
That means they'll hire you.

92
00:05:35,064 --> 00:05:36,774
I didn't get an official offer yet,

93
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,943
but I must say it's most likely.

94
00:05:39,026 --> 00:05:40,403
An attorney at K and L Law Firm!

95
00:05:40,486 --> 00:05:43,656
What a great honor for our family!

96
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,324
Hold on.

97
00:05:45,408 --> 00:05:49,120
Attention, please!

98
00:05:49,203 --> 00:05:50,997
Each table will have

99
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,166
a bottle of soju on the house today!

100
00:05:53,249 --> 00:05:54,292
- Oh, my.
- Really?

101
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:55,835
The owner's insane.

102
00:05:55,918 --> 00:05:56,794
Drink up!

103
00:06:00,256 --> 00:06:02,175
One serving of pork belly
on the house too.

104
00:06:02,258 --> 00:06:05,052
- Oh, goodness.
- My mother-in-law never disappoints.

105
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,848
Just one serving, not two.

106
00:06:13,060 --> 00:06:14,729
- A bottle of beer, please.
- Here too.

107
00:06:15,646 --> 00:06:17,064
Coming right away.

108
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,986
WE REGRET TO INFORM YOU THAT
WE WON'T MOVE FORWARD WITH YOU

109
00:06:22,570 --> 00:06:23,821
This can't be.

110
00:06:33,039 --> 00:06:34,040
Okay.

111
00:06:35,249 --> 00:06:36,667
I was too naive.

112
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:40,880
There.

113
00:06:45,176 --> 00:06:47,053
WE REGRET TO INFORM YOU
OF UNFORTUNATE NEWS

114
00:06:47,136 --> 00:06:48,596
Are you serious?

115
00:06:51,724 --> 00:06:53,267
YOUR APPLICATION
WAS NOT SELECTED

116
00:06:53,851 --> 00:06:55,728
What on earth is the problem?

117
00:07:02,026 --> 00:07:03,653
LAWSUIT FOR DAMAGES
PLAINTIFF: SEONGHO ELECTRONICS

118
00:07:16,332 --> 00:07:18,417
- This is about Haeseong Trading.
- Thank you.

119
00:07:18,501 --> 00:07:20,836
This is the petition
for Myeongjin Construction.

120
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,464
- I placed the materials on your desk too.
- Okay.

121
00:07:25,383 --> 00:07:27,593
TAEBAEK LAW FIRM
PARTNER HAN NA-HYUN

122
00:07:40,982 --> 00:07:42,191
Hello.

123
00:07:43,317 --> 00:07:46,237
Seongho Electronics' chairman
was greatly satisfied.

124
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,072
He wants to sign a partnership with us.

125
00:07:48,155 --> 00:07:49,448
That's good.

126
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:52,451
You seem busy. Do you want me
to interview the applicants?

127
00:07:52,535 --> 00:07:54,662
It's about my future associate.
I'll do it myself.

128
00:07:54,745 --> 00:07:56,664
I have about 20 minutes.

129
00:07:56,747 --> 00:07:57,957
Then, just refer to this.

130
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:00,251
What is it?

131
00:08:07,216 --> 00:08:10,511
THE 2025 ENTRY-LEVEL
ASSOCIATE INTERVIEW

132
00:08:13,139 --> 00:08:14,515
INTERVIEW ADMISSION TICKET
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

133
00:08:14,599 --> 00:08:15,850
Next applicant, please come in.

134
00:08:15,933 --> 00:08:16,809
Okay.

135
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:25,484
INTERVIEW ROOM

136
00:08:32,575 --> 00:08:34,910
Hello, my name is Shin I-rang.

137
00:08:34,994 --> 00:08:36,287
Hello, please have a seat.

138
00:08:38,247 --> 00:08:39,999
Attorney Han, ask questions first.

139
00:08:43,252 --> 00:08:44,837
I don't have any questions

140
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,631
for Mr. Shin.

141
00:08:48,466 --> 00:08:51,510
I'm sure he knows why.

142
00:08:52,094 --> 00:08:52,928
Let's move on.

143
00:08:55,348 --> 00:08:57,016
He's the last applicant.

144
00:09:18,621 --> 00:09:19,622
What are you doing?

145
00:09:20,206 --> 00:09:21,874
Let me ask the same question.

146
00:09:27,463 --> 00:09:28,714
A scarlet letter…

147
00:09:30,049 --> 00:09:31,342
As expected.

148
00:09:41,477 --> 00:09:43,979
Were you aware
of your husband's corruption?

149
00:09:44,063 --> 00:09:45,898
What do you think you're doing?

150
00:09:45,981 --> 00:09:48,109
Have you no manners at all?

151
00:09:48,192 --> 00:09:50,736
- Do you admit to his crimes?
- Get out.

152
00:09:50,820 --> 00:09:53,989
My dad wasn't a criminal.

153
00:09:54,073 --> 00:09:56,617
He was a prosecutor
who punished bad people!

154
00:10:07,837 --> 00:10:08,796
I'm turning you down.

155
00:10:10,548 --> 00:10:11,465
I am…

156
00:10:13,008 --> 00:10:14,468
turning you down first.

157
00:10:29,567 --> 00:10:31,527
You should've at least asked
routine questions.

158
00:10:33,446 --> 00:10:35,740
He needs to know how the world sees him.

159
00:10:37,533 --> 00:10:39,326
Only then, he'll stop biting on granite.

160
00:10:42,705 --> 00:10:43,914
I'll be off since we're done.

161
00:10:51,338 --> 00:10:54,216
A father's actions from 20 years ago

162
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:55,885
is causing harm to his son.

163
00:10:56,552 --> 00:10:57,970
How cruel.

164
00:10:58,596 --> 00:11:01,724
Is it because the judge and prosecutor
related to it haven't retired yet?

165
00:11:02,391 --> 00:11:03,684
Maybe.

166
00:11:06,061 --> 00:11:07,980
This won't do. Just change your name.

167
00:11:08,689 --> 00:11:11,525
Put all the past behind you
and make a new start with a new--

168
00:11:13,235 --> 00:11:14,403
No.

169
00:11:14,487 --> 00:11:17,406
Now that I know how the world sees me,

170
00:11:18,949 --> 00:11:20,367
I won't stay still.

171
00:11:22,036 --> 00:11:22,870
You know what?

172
00:11:24,497 --> 00:11:28,542
I'm going to make the best law firm ever
under my own name.

173
00:11:30,419 --> 00:11:31,378
And then,

174
00:11:32,213 --> 00:11:36,217
I'm going to have all those
who mistreated me line up in two rows.

175
00:11:41,013 --> 00:11:43,599
I'll take good revenge on them.

176
00:11:43,682 --> 00:11:44,683
Wait and see.

177
00:11:59,573 --> 00:12:00,574
What?

178
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:05,454
Are you pleased
to have ruined your son's future?

179
00:12:07,289 --> 00:12:08,290
Fine.

180
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:12,378
Let's see who wins.

181
00:12:13,254 --> 00:12:14,255
Bring it on!

182
00:13:30,956 --> 00:13:34,668
EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES

183
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:42,343
MR. KIM'S REAL ESTATE OFFICE

184
00:13:48,641 --> 00:13:50,351
4,305,100 WON

185
00:13:50,934 --> 00:13:52,144
Would this be enough?

186
00:14:01,445 --> 00:14:02,821
What brings you here, I-rang?

187
00:14:04,782 --> 00:14:06,408
The thing is…

188
00:14:07,826 --> 00:14:10,079
Your mother must've sent you.

189
00:14:10,162 --> 00:14:11,080
What?

190
00:14:11,914 --> 00:14:13,332
After all,

191
00:14:13,415 --> 00:14:15,417
an attorney should
take charge of a contract.

192
00:14:16,293 --> 00:14:19,296
Please do the rest, okay?

193
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:21,757
Where's Mr. Kim, though?

194
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:22,841
Oh.

195
00:14:23,384 --> 00:14:24,885
Someone passed out or something.

196
00:14:24,969 --> 00:14:26,637
He'll be back soon.

197
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:27,763
I'm a detective this time.

198
00:14:28,555 --> 00:14:29,598
See you.

199
00:14:38,399 --> 00:14:40,401
This must be Mom's lease contract.

200
00:14:41,068 --> 00:14:42,152
COMMERCIAL LEASE AGREEMENT

201
00:14:42,236 --> 00:14:43,445
The deposit's 200 million won?

202
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,949
I didn't know Mom was this rich.

203
00:14:47,866 --> 00:14:48,867
Hold on.

204
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:50,911
Two hundred million won?

205
00:14:53,914 --> 00:14:56,667
Why be a shaman
if you can't even tell your own future?

206
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,085
Hello.

207
00:14:58,168 --> 00:14:59,503
Oh, my.

208
00:14:59,586 --> 00:15:01,422
What brings you here, Mr. Attorney?

209
00:15:01,505 --> 00:15:03,215
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

210
00:15:03,298 --> 00:15:05,342
Are you here to renew
the butcher shop contract?

211
00:15:07,219 --> 00:15:08,470
The thing is,

212
00:15:08,554 --> 00:15:11,181
were you the landlord of my mom's shop?

213
00:15:11,765 --> 00:15:12,599
You didn't know?

214
00:15:14,768 --> 00:15:17,146
Mr. Kim, I need your help.

215
00:15:17,855 --> 00:15:19,064
You need my help?

216
00:15:19,148 --> 00:15:21,442
I need to open a law office,

217
00:15:21,525 --> 00:15:24,737
so please let me use 30 million won
from her deposit.

218
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,822
What?

219
00:15:26,905 --> 00:15:28,407
That's out of the question.

220
00:15:29,825 --> 00:15:31,618
I'll pay 10% more of the commission.

221
00:15:32,703 --> 00:15:35,456
- And I'll provide you with legal services.
- Indefinitely?

222
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:39,877
- Deal.
- What's the condition?

223
00:15:40,461 --> 00:15:42,004
I'd like a courthouse view.

224
00:15:42,588 --> 00:15:44,089
A close-up courthouse view.

225
00:15:44,173 --> 00:15:47,509
You can't rent out an office like that
with a 30-million-won deposit.

226
00:15:48,761 --> 00:15:49,762
Is that so?

227
00:15:51,180 --> 00:15:52,181
I-rang.

228
00:15:53,223 --> 00:15:54,349
There may be one.

229
00:15:55,601 --> 00:15:56,435
Really?

230
00:15:56,518 --> 00:15:57,352
Yes.

231
00:15:57,436 --> 00:16:00,814
OPEN

232
00:16:11,408 --> 00:16:13,077
Come on. You're young enough for this.

233
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,329
It's a quiet neighborhood.

234
00:16:15,412 --> 00:16:16,455
Over there.

235
00:16:19,917 --> 00:16:22,753
This is the one right here.

236
00:16:22,836 --> 00:16:23,837
OKCHEON BUILDING

237
00:16:25,756 --> 00:16:28,467
I didn't know this neighborhood
had a building like this.

238
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:32,137
Oh, perfect.
The wallpapering must be over.

239
00:16:32,221 --> 00:16:33,388
- Mr. Park!
- Hello.

240
00:16:33,472 --> 00:16:34,723
I appreciate the hard work.

241
00:16:34,807 --> 00:16:36,767
We're all done. Thank you.

242
00:16:37,810 --> 00:16:38,936
Come along.

243
00:16:46,026 --> 00:16:48,862
All of this will get moved out.

244
00:16:52,491 --> 00:16:54,076
- It's here.
- Here?

245
00:16:54,159 --> 00:16:56,328
FOR LEASE

246
00:17:07,339 --> 00:17:08,841
The interior is quite unique.

247
00:17:09,424 --> 00:17:10,801
The landlord has elegant taste.

248
00:17:15,973 --> 00:17:19,309
Oh, these.
The former tenant left them behind.

249
00:17:19,393 --> 00:17:21,311
I'll throw them out, so don't bother.

250
00:17:21,395 --> 00:17:23,272
You can leave them here.

251
00:17:23,355 --> 00:17:24,773
It takes work to throw them out.

252
00:17:25,774 --> 00:17:27,067
Let's save the Earth.

253
00:17:30,571 --> 00:17:33,323
Anyway, what was this place?

254
00:17:34,449 --> 00:17:35,993
- A Chinese restaurant?
- What?

255
00:17:36,076 --> 00:17:38,829
Oh, what's the word?

256
00:17:39,371 --> 00:17:41,790
You know,
something about foreseeing the future…

257
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,626
An AI company? Big data?

258
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:45,544
What?

259
00:17:46,545 --> 00:17:49,339
Yeah, I think it was something like that.

260
00:17:52,342 --> 00:17:55,220
Don't you smell something weird?

261
00:17:56,263 --> 00:17:57,848
It's coming from the wallpaper.

262
00:17:57,931 --> 00:17:59,683
It will go away soon. Don't bother it.

263
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:04,563
There's no place like this
in the neighborhood.

264
00:18:04,646 --> 00:18:07,024
The heavens really helped you out here.

265
00:18:07,107 --> 00:18:08,817
You may trick a ghost, but not me.

266
00:18:08,901 --> 00:18:10,819
I know there are
many empty offices these days.

267
00:18:12,779 --> 00:18:14,573
Wait, I-rang.

268
00:18:14,656 --> 00:18:16,074
You wanted a view, didn't you?

269
00:18:16,742 --> 00:18:17,826
Come here.

270
00:18:24,374 --> 00:18:25,500
Isn't it nice?

271
00:18:26,418 --> 00:18:27,586
Breathtaking, right?

272
00:18:58,492 --> 00:19:01,870
There's no other place with a
courthouse view like this at your budget.

273
00:19:01,954 --> 00:19:03,538
Think wisely.

274
00:19:05,582 --> 00:19:06,792
I'll take it.

275
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:07,918
I like it.

276
00:19:13,340 --> 00:19:15,592
Good thinking.

277
00:19:17,761 --> 00:19:19,513
Yahoo.

278
00:19:24,518 --> 00:19:27,396
Please place it all the way
at the top of the building

279
00:19:27,479 --> 00:19:29,189
so that it's visible from the courthouse.

280
00:19:32,859 --> 00:19:35,362
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

281
00:19:50,043 --> 00:19:52,337
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

282
00:19:52,421 --> 00:19:55,757
It sure is in my blood to run a business.

283
00:20:06,685 --> 00:20:07,686
What was that?

284
00:20:15,777 --> 00:20:16,945
What is this?

285
00:20:34,296 --> 00:20:35,297
Is this incense?

286
00:20:37,341 --> 00:20:39,676
Nice. The air was musty anyway.

287
00:20:52,105 --> 00:20:53,190
I like it.

288
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:28,141
Huh?

289
00:21:29,101 --> 00:21:30,102
Was it a dream?

290
00:21:35,857 --> 00:21:36,858
Hi.

291
00:21:36,942 --> 00:21:38,193
Hi, I-rang.

292
00:21:38,276 --> 00:21:39,611
Remember the man you mentioned?

293
00:21:39,694 --> 00:21:41,029
Man?

294
00:21:41,113 --> 00:21:42,114
Who?

295
00:21:42,197 --> 00:21:44,408
You asked me to set you up
with a paralegal.

296
00:21:44,491 --> 00:21:46,201
He's already here.

297
00:21:46,284 --> 00:21:47,869
Let me call you later.

298
00:21:47,953 --> 00:21:49,371
What… Hello?

299
00:21:50,288 --> 00:21:52,916
No, he's already hired.
That's why I called.

300
00:21:52,999 --> 00:21:54,334
He came? Who is he talking about?

301
00:21:55,585 --> 00:21:56,586
You're here early.

302
00:21:57,587 --> 00:21:58,672
You must've waited long.

303
00:21:58,755 --> 00:22:00,757
I don't usually sleep in like that

304
00:22:00,841 --> 00:22:02,592
but I've been stressed out lately.

305
00:22:04,636 --> 00:22:06,012
You can see me?

306
00:22:06,805 --> 00:22:07,806
Pardon?

307
00:22:07,889 --> 00:22:09,850
Yes, that's why I'm talking to you.

308
00:22:15,939 --> 00:22:19,067
I'm quite tall myself,

309
00:22:19,151 --> 00:22:20,610
but you're really tall.

310
00:22:21,945 --> 00:22:22,988
Are you 190 cm tall?

311
00:22:23,071 --> 00:22:24,406
Maybe 2 m?

312
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:42,841
Y-You…

313
00:22:42,924 --> 00:22:44,593
W-What is it?

314
00:22:44,676 --> 00:22:46,344
G-Ghost…

315
00:22:51,266 --> 00:22:52,267
Ghost!

316
00:22:52,350 --> 00:22:53,977
- It's a ghost!
- Oh, dear.

317
00:22:57,647 --> 00:22:59,941
Dear God, Jesus Christ, and Virgin Mary,
please forgive me.

318
00:23:00,442 --> 00:23:03,195
I'll pay off Mom's deposit
and turn over a new leaf.

319
00:23:03,278 --> 00:23:05,113
Please don't let me die.

320
00:23:06,114 --> 00:23:07,240
What are you doing?

321
00:23:07,324 --> 00:23:08,700
Do you want to play hide-and-seek?

322
00:23:10,827 --> 00:23:13,371
Oh, my. That must be painful.

323
00:23:14,122 --> 00:23:16,875
Go away! Go!

324
00:23:16,958 --> 00:23:17,959
Go away…

325
00:24:00,085 --> 00:24:01,461
An AI company?

326
00:24:01,544 --> 00:24:02,921
Big data?

327
00:24:04,673 --> 00:24:06,007
He lied to me.

328
00:24:10,345 --> 00:24:11,346
I can't believe this.

329
00:24:13,306 --> 00:24:14,516
Look.

330
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:17,519
Ghosts don't exist,
especially in this day and age.

331
00:24:17,602 --> 00:24:19,646
A shaman must've summoned him.

332
00:24:19,729 --> 00:24:21,106
What shaman?

333
00:24:23,108 --> 00:24:25,360
Fine, here.

334
00:24:26,111 --> 00:24:27,946
This is the evidence.

335
00:24:28,488 --> 00:24:31,199
You deceived me into signing this lease,
so call it off.

336
00:24:31,283 --> 00:24:32,742
Nowhere in real estate law

337
00:24:32,826 --> 00:24:36,788
is there an obligation to notify
who the former tenant was.

338
00:24:38,873 --> 00:24:39,874
There's more.

339
00:24:40,375 --> 00:24:42,585
Article 4, Paragraph 5
of the contract says,

340
00:24:42,669 --> 00:24:45,630
"The tenant may cancel the contract

341
00:24:45,714 --> 00:24:48,133
if they have not been notified
of any undesirable facility."

342
00:24:48,216 --> 00:24:50,927
A haunted place is clearly
an undesirable facility.

343
00:24:51,928 --> 00:24:53,513
So, you'll go by the book?

344
00:24:53,596 --> 00:24:56,391
Then, prove that there are ghosts here.

345
00:24:56,474 --> 00:24:57,475
Unbelievable.

346
00:25:00,228 --> 00:25:01,896
There he is. He's here.

347
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:02,981
Over there.

348
00:25:03,064 --> 00:25:03,898
Where?

349
00:25:05,483 --> 00:25:06,526
There!

350
00:25:06,609 --> 00:25:08,236
There. He's there!

351
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:09,821
Where?

352
00:25:09,904 --> 00:25:10,947
Do you really not see him?

353
00:25:11,031 --> 00:25:12,866
See what?

354
00:25:13,450 --> 00:25:15,035
Snap out of it, I-rang.

355
00:25:15,577 --> 00:25:16,536
What a shame.

356
00:25:16,619 --> 00:25:18,621
This is driving me nuts!

357
00:25:22,542 --> 00:25:23,835
Maybe that's it.

358
00:25:23,918 --> 00:25:25,211
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

359
00:25:28,965 --> 00:25:31,176
There's this tale
called the Legend of Arang.

360
00:25:31,843 --> 00:25:34,054
Every time a new district magistrate
is appointed,

361
00:25:34,137 --> 00:25:36,681
a resentful virgin ghost visits him.

362
00:25:37,474 --> 00:25:40,810
And it kills all the feeble magistrates.

363
00:25:46,941 --> 00:25:47,901
This is killing me.

364
00:25:49,444 --> 00:25:50,779
Wake up.

365
00:25:50,862 --> 00:25:51,863
It's a dream.

366
00:25:55,075 --> 00:25:56,284
But then,

367
00:25:56,368 --> 00:25:59,120
- a brave magistrate survives…
- Hear me out!

368
00:25:59,204 --> 00:26:01,831
…and helps her
resolve her resentment at last

369
00:26:01,915 --> 00:26:05,251
in this beautiful tale.

370
00:26:07,295 --> 00:26:09,005
Beautiful, my foot.

371
00:26:10,507 --> 00:26:12,759
What are you looking at?
You're not even a virgin ghost.

372
00:26:13,551 --> 00:26:14,427
I'm sorry.

373
00:26:15,595 --> 00:26:16,721
He spoke.

374
00:26:16,805 --> 00:26:19,516
Mr. Kim, did you hear him?
He spoke just now.

375
00:26:20,308 --> 00:26:21,893
Wow.

376
00:26:21,976 --> 00:26:24,187
You're good at acting.

377
00:26:26,272 --> 00:26:28,358
Still, no. I won't back down.

378
00:26:28,441 --> 00:26:29,275
Neither will I.

379
00:26:29,359 --> 00:26:32,070
I absolutely will not use this office.

380
00:26:32,153 --> 00:26:34,531
If you refuse, I'll take you to court.

381
00:26:35,156 --> 00:26:36,699
That leaves me no choice,

382
00:26:36,783 --> 00:26:38,451
but to discuss this with Ms. Park.

383
00:26:38,952 --> 00:26:40,578
I wonder if she's done butchering.

384
00:26:40,662 --> 00:26:42,455
I hope she has some energy left.

385
00:26:45,125 --> 00:26:48,086
Who scares you more? Ghosts or your mom?

386
00:27:01,224 --> 00:27:04,978
I'll give you a few days
until rent is due, okay?

387
00:27:09,983 --> 00:27:11,484
Wait for me, Mr. Kim!

388
00:27:17,031 --> 00:27:18,700
You have until tomorrow to leave.

389
00:27:18,783 --> 00:27:19,909
Otherwise,

390
00:27:19,993 --> 00:27:21,828
I'll come with a cross and a Bible.

391
00:27:29,294 --> 00:27:32,505
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

392
00:27:33,256 --> 00:27:34,132
Eat up.

393
00:27:34,966 --> 00:27:36,509
Uncle!

394
00:27:36,593 --> 00:27:38,052
Hi, Da-bong.

395
00:27:38,136 --> 00:27:41,473
You always come
every time we're having something yummy.

396
00:27:41,556 --> 00:27:42,724
Da-bong.

397
00:27:42,807 --> 00:27:44,267
Were you eating a lot?

398
00:27:44,350 --> 00:27:47,187
I expected you'd have dinner outside
and didn't prepare your share.

399
00:27:47,270 --> 00:27:49,105
It's okay.
I'll just have what's on the table.

400
00:27:49,898 --> 00:27:51,566
- Hold on.
- Well…

401
00:27:55,487 --> 00:27:56,404
You must be tired.

402
00:27:57,113 --> 00:27:59,199
- Let me go make some stew.
- Thanks.

403
00:27:59,282 --> 00:28:01,659
Have some of this first.

404
00:28:03,119 --> 00:28:04,496
Goodness.

405
00:28:05,038 --> 00:28:07,624
Uncle, why aren't you having pork belly?

406
00:28:07,707 --> 00:28:08,875
It's delicious.

407
00:28:10,084 --> 00:28:11,336
I'm allergic to pork.

408
00:28:11,419 --> 00:28:12,462
If I have pork belly…

409
00:28:12,545 --> 00:28:13,713
Then, what?

410
00:28:33,441 --> 00:28:35,276
Goodness, it's…

411
00:28:36,319 --> 00:28:37,612
It's needless to say.

412
00:28:39,072 --> 00:28:40,323
This is to die for.

413
00:28:47,163 --> 00:28:48,331
You…

414
00:28:48,915 --> 00:28:50,166
What?

415
00:28:50,250 --> 00:28:51,376
What are you looking at?

416
00:28:51,459 --> 00:28:53,545
Have you never seen
someone eat meat or what?

417
00:28:53,628 --> 00:28:55,088
That's right.

418
00:28:55,171 --> 00:28:57,173
I've never seen Shin I-rang have meat!

419
00:28:58,132 --> 00:28:59,008
Uncle.

420
00:28:59,092 --> 00:29:00,802
Your cheeks are red.

421
00:29:00,885 --> 00:29:02,387
Just like a monkey's butt.

422
00:29:02,470 --> 00:29:03,304
What?

423
00:29:04,013 --> 00:29:04,848
What about my cheeks?

424
00:29:04,931 --> 00:29:06,808
Hey! Hey, you brat.

425
00:29:08,059 --> 00:29:10,937
You shouldn't be eating pork!
Or you'll get rashes.

426
00:29:11,437 --> 00:29:14,274
Look at your face. It's already red.

427
00:29:19,988 --> 00:29:22,323
- I-rang.
- Unbelievable.

428
00:29:24,284 --> 00:29:26,870
Just why are you doing this to me?!

429
00:29:27,620 --> 00:29:29,747
Why do you have to give me a hard time?

430
00:29:30,248 --> 00:29:32,917
Please leave me be!

431
00:29:34,210 --> 00:29:38,381
"He was with the wild animals,

432
00:29:39,382 --> 00:29:42,510
and angels…

433
00:29:43,845 --> 00:29:44,888
attended him."

434
00:29:46,431 --> 00:29:48,141
"After John was put"--

435
00:29:50,226 --> 00:29:51,811
What do you want from me?

436
00:29:51,895 --> 00:29:54,022
Who are you in the first place?

437
00:29:54,606 --> 00:29:55,481
I don't know myself.

438
00:29:55,565 --> 00:29:57,650
This is insane.

439
00:29:58,568 --> 00:30:00,695
Look. Since you're an attorney,

440
00:30:01,446 --> 00:30:03,239
can't you look into who I am?

441
00:30:03,323 --> 00:30:04,324
Why should I do that?

442
00:30:04,908 --> 00:30:07,493
I have to pay rent starting next month.

443
00:30:08,286 --> 00:30:10,246
Otherwise, my mom will kill me.

444
00:30:10,747 --> 00:30:12,790
Bring me money or…

445
00:30:13,374 --> 00:30:14,959
get me winning lottery numbers.

446
00:30:15,043 --> 00:30:17,337
If I had such power,

447
00:30:17,420 --> 00:30:20,340
I would've bought a building
in the other world.

448
00:30:20,423 --> 00:30:23,051
Is all you can do startling me, then?

449
00:30:24,093 --> 00:30:25,511
How pathetic.

450
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:29,933
A ghost?

451
00:30:30,516 --> 00:30:32,352
I think I got possessed
at a shaman's house.

452
00:30:33,311 --> 00:30:36,439
That shaman had been taken to a hospital,
but he was nowhere to be found.

453
00:30:37,106 --> 00:30:38,942
He ran off
without paying the hospital fee.

454
00:30:39,943 --> 00:30:41,903
How did you come to see that ghost?

455
00:30:42,487 --> 00:30:44,906
There was a desk that used to be his.

456
00:30:45,490 --> 00:30:47,825
I found an old incense burner
in the drawer.

457
00:30:52,747 --> 00:30:53,790
It's cold.

458
00:30:58,336 --> 00:30:59,462
That's cold.

459
00:31:00,171 --> 00:31:01,005
How strange.

460
00:31:01,589 --> 00:31:04,634
In most cases, the body twists
or the holy water makes smoke.

461
00:31:05,259 --> 00:31:07,178
This is not an ordinary ghost.

462
00:31:07,261 --> 00:31:09,430
He reads the Bible,
and he enjoys eating pork belly with soju…

463
00:31:09,514 --> 00:31:11,391
He even drinks coffee.

464
00:31:11,474 --> 00:31:12,934
Maybe he used to like having those.

465
00:31:13,017 --> 00:31:14,686
Being possessed

466
00:31:14,769 --> 00:31:17,188
manifests when their desires reach a peak.

467
00:31:18,064 --> 00:31:21,526
When something triggers a rush of joy,
like their favorite food or song,

468
00:31:21,609 --> 00:31:22,694
or oppositely,

469
00:31:22,777 --> 00:31:24,487
when they're faced with someone they hate

470
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:26,572
or something that causes rage,

471
00:31:26,656 --> 00:31:27,949
the possibility of possession increases.

472
00:31:29,033 --> 00:31:30,535
Once you're possessed,

473
00:31:30,618 --> 00:31:32,870
you'd make absurd behaviors

474
00:31:32,954 --> 00:31:35,456
while you don't even remember

475
00:31:36,666 --> 00:31:38,042
what you've even done.

476
00:31:38,126 --> 00:31:39,961
That means I'm in a dangerous situation.

477
00:31:40,044 --> 00:31:41,087
Whether you are or not,

478
00:31:41,713 --> 00:31:44,882
let's go to Okcheon Building and check.

479
00:31:48,302 --> 00:31:49,846
Seriously!

480
00:31:53,599 --> 00:31:54,892
This is as expected.

481
00:31:55,810 --> 00:31:58,771
These talismans are summoning ghosts.

482
00:31:59,731 --> 00:32:02,358
If I burn the talismans,

483
00:32:02,442 --> 00:32:03,568
will the ghost disappear?

484
00:32:05,028 --> 00:32:05,862
Probably.

485
00:32:06,904 --> 00:32:07,947
No.

486
00:32:08,031 --> 00:32:09,907
Never, not until I find out who I am!

487
00:32:09,991 --> 00:32:11,784
You don't have a say here.

488
00:32:13,703 --> 00:32:15,580
Is he here right now? What did he say?

489
00:32:15,663 --> 00:32:16,956
What is he claiming?

490
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:19,834
He's been grilling me
to find out who he is.

491
00:32:19,917 --> 00:32:22,295
Then, why don't you
look into who this ghost is?

492
00:32:22,879 --> 00:32:25,089
It's easy to help a spirit pass on
if you know their story.

493
00:32:25,173 --> 00:32:28,259
Do it for me. Do it!

494
00:32:28,342 --> 00:32:29,177
Do it…

495
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:33,056
Even if I'm to help him,

496
00:32:33,139 --> 00:32:34,724
I don't know how.

497
00:32:34,807 --> 00:32:37,143
With his name and date of birth,

498
00:32:37,226 --> 00:32:38,478
he'll regain his memory.

499
00:32:39,020 --> 00:32:39,854
Are you serious?

500
00:32:40,438 --> 00:32:42,982
How do you know that?

501
00:32:43,066 --> 00:32:44,233
Oh, I was…

502
00:32:45,526 --> 00:32:47,695
once a shaman.

503
00:32:56,037 --> 00:32:58,915
And God's embrace has changed me

504
00:33:00,166 --> 00:33:01,501
like this.

505
00:33:05,797 --> 00:33:09,008
Come to think of it,
it won't be hard to find out who he is.

506
00:33:09,884 --> 00:33:12,345
You just need to check it
with whoever visited the shaman.

507
00:33:12,428 --> 00:33:14,972
That person must've wanted
to summon the ghost.

508
00:33:15,056 --> 00:33:16,140
I see.

509
00:33:16,891 --> 00:33:19,143
I saw there was
a security camera in the hallway.

510
00:33:26,567 --> 00:33:27,819
Is this all?

511
00:33:28,653 --> 00:33:29,987
There aren't enough materials.

512
00:33:30,571 --> 00:33:31,823
We don't need materials.

513
00:33:32,573 --> 00:33:34,117
The bereaved want to settle.

514
00:33:35,368 --> 00:33:36,828
I just want you to follow up on it.

515
00:33:36,911 --> 00:33:39,247
Well, a peaceful settlement is
the best option,

516
00:33:39,831 --> 00:33:41,624
but just in case it goes south,

517
00:33:41,707 --> 00:33:43,918
I'll make sure
to get the bereaved's signature.

518
00:33:44,544 --> 00:33:45,586
That sounds better.

519
00:33:49,799 --> 00:33:51,634
SARANG VOLUNTEERS

520
00:33:53,177 --> 00:33:55,138
This woman was the last visitor.

521
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:56,806
Look here.

522
00:33:57,598 --> 00:33:59,350
She visited several times.

523
00:34:00,059 --> 00:34:02,603
Sir, when was this captured?

524
00:34:03,271 --> 00:34:04,188
Oh, that?

525
00:34:04,272 --> 00:34:05,523
That's a live feed.

526
00:34:05,606 --> 00:34:06,732
What?

527
00:34:06,816 --> 00:34:10,820
I'm saying that the woman is standing
in front of Unit 501 right now.

528
00:34:16,784 --> 00:34:18,828
How may I help you?

529
00:34:18,911 --> 00:34:20,371
Well…

530
00:34:21,539 --> 00:34:24,834
It was a male shaman's place
until recently…

531
00:34:26,002 --> 00:34:28,629
The shaman left due to illness.

532
00:34:29,297 --> 00:34:30,298
Yes, I know.

533
00:34:30,798 --> 00:34:34,385
I was with him when he passed out.

534
00:34:38,598 --> 00:34:40,433
I called an ambulance too.

535
00:34:41,642 --> 00:34:43,728
I came out of concern

536
00:34:43,811 --> 00:34:47,440
and decided to enter because it was
changed to an attorney's office.

537
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:53,571
Did you perhaps visit the shaman
regarding your husband?

538
00:34:54,614 --> 00:34:56,240
How did you know?

539
00:34:56,324 --> 00:34:58,659
Go ahead and tell me what happened.

540
00:35:00,036 --> 00:35:03,372
Both attorneys and shamans are there
to hear stories of those who were wronged.

541
00:35:09,170 --> 00:35:10,129
A few months…

542
00:35:12,882 --> 00:35:13,925
A few months ago,

543
00:35:15,218 --> 00:35:19,347
my husband had surgery
at Cheongil Hospital.

544
00:35:20,306 --> 00:35:21,432
He went into shock

545
00:35:22,141 --> 00:35:23,726
during the surgery.

546
00:35:24,769 --> 00:35:28,022
Is that why you visited the shaman?

547
00:35:28,606 --> 00:35:30,483
To say your last goodbye?

548
00:35:30,566 --> 00:35:31,609
No.

549
00:35:33,027 --> 00:35:34,111
Since then,

550
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:38,282
my daughter won't come out of her room.

551
00:35:42,119 --> 00:35:43,079
Open the door.

552
00:35:43,996 --> 00:35:46,666
- Her healthy dad died out of the blue.
- Open up.

553
00:35:47,959 --> 00:35:49,210
It must've shocked her badly.

554
00:35:49,293 --> 00:35:50,628
Come on, say something.

555
00:35:57,301 --> 00:35:58,177
Ji-woo!

556
00:36:01,264 --> 00:36:04,267
I won't do it again, so please…

557
00:36:12,233 --> 00:36:14,819
She's locked herself in her room
for five months.

558
00:36:16,529 --> 00:36:17,613
I've tried to persuade her

559
00:36:18,656 --> 00:36:21,492
softly, with anger, and in tears.

560
00:36:23,536 --> 00:36:24,745
But none of it worked.

561
00:36:29,792 --> 00:36:30,626
At least,

562
00:36:32,503 --> 00:36:34,005
it feels a little better

563
00:36:34,964 --> 00:36:36,340
to open up to you like this.

564
00:36:38,676 --> 00:36:39,844
Thank you.

565
00:36:42,513 --> 00:36:45,391
M-My name. My name and date of birth.

566
00:36:46,392 --> 00:36:47,643
Could you tell me

567
00:36:49,729 --> 00:36:52,690
your husband's name and date of birth?

568
00:36:53,357 --> 00:36:55,943
His name is Lee Gang-pung.

569
00:36:57,528 --> 00:36:58,988
He was born

570
00:37:00,197 --> 00:37:02,283
on April 25, 1980.

571
00:37:22,762 --> 00:37:24,764
My dear puppy is awake.

572
00:37:32,146 --> 00:37:33,689
You're pretty just like your mom.

573
00:37:34,732 --> 00:37:36,275
I'm a dad now.

574
00:37:42,656 --> 00:37:44,116
Thank you.

575
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,993
Look. You're like a newlywed.

576
00:37:46,077 --> 00:37:47,328
Careful.

577
00:37:47,411 --> 00:37:48,871
SARANG VOLUNTEERS

578
00:37:51,457 --> 00:37:52,416
Bingo!

579
00:37:52,500 --> 00:37:53,334
What do you think?

580
00:38:10,393 --> 00:38:11,310
Min-ju!

581
00:38:20,277 --> 00:38:21,404
You must've

582
00:38:22,446 --> 00:38:25,157
struggled so much alone.

583
00:38:37,503 --> 00:38:38,587
Are you out of your mind?

584
00:38:46,887 --> 00:38:48,806
Why did she slap me?

585
00:39:05,614 --> 00:39:08,617
What happened all of a sudden?

586
00:39:09,201 --> 00:39:10,077
I…

587
00:39:11,787 --> 00:39:12,913
remembered.

588
00:39:14,874 --> 00:39:15,875
Really?

589
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:17,835
My death…

590
00:39:18,627 --> 00:39:21,046
Please administer anesthesia.

591
00:39:24,049 --> 00:39:25,551
He's going under.

592
00:39:34,018 --> 00:39:36,479
His airway is blocked.
We must perform emergency surgery now!

593
00:39:39,398 --> 00:39:41,358
- Damn it!
- Should we prepare for a tracheostomy?

594
00:39:41,442 --> 00:39:43,360
- Doctor!
- Shut up!

595
00:39:43,444 --> 00:39:44,862
I'll handle it, okay?

596
00:39:56,290 --> 00:39:57,291
Keep this a secret.

597
00:39:59,710 --> 00:40:02,213
We'll just say he died from shock
due to cardiac arrest.

598
00:40:05,549 --> 00:40:07,092
I clearly heard a voice…

599
00:40:09,094 --> 00:40:11,388
urging to frame it as death from shock.

600
00:40:25,528 --> 00:40:27,571
He never puts his clothes
in the washing machine.

601
00:40:46,465 --> 00:40:49,218
JOB APPLICATION
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

602
00:41:22,585 --> 00:41:24,169
Why aren't you asleep?

603
00:41:24,253 --> 00:41:26,046
Oh, I couldn't sleep.

604
00:41:27,506 --> 00:41:28,882
I should go to bed now.

605
00:41:29,675 --> 00:41:31,260
I'm going to have a drink.

606
00:41:32,261 --> 00:41:33,304
Care to join me?

607
00:41:34,346 --> 00:41:35,931
There's no drinking snack.

608
00:41:37,141 --> 00:41:39,143
Soju is best when you drink it neat.

609
00:41:45,107 --> 00:41:46,317
Cheers.

610
00:41:58,370 --> 00:41:59,330
Son.

611
00:42:00,289 --> 00:42:01,498
Is life hard these days?

612
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:06,295
When was it ever not tough?

613
00:42:08,547 --> 00:42:11,050
It took me five years
to barely get a law license.

614
00:42:12,676 --> 00:42:13,761
And I barely got a job.

615
00:42:15,387 --> 00:42:17,723
Still, you've pulled it all through.

616
00:42:19,725 --> 00:42:21,685
You're right, but…

617
00:42:24,104 --> 00:42:27,483
How much does it cost
to open a law office?

618
00:42:29,860 --> 00:42:34,031
That senior of yours named Jeong-su
or whatever even bought a building.

619
00:42:34,114 --> 00:42:35,282
What are you saying?

620
00:42:35,991 --> 00:42:38,035
You said I was too soft
to run a legal office.

621
00:42:38,118 --> 00:42:40,996
That was to prevent you

622
00:42:41,080 --> 00:42:43,374
from getting ahead of yourself
in the beginning.

623
00:42:46,377 --> 00:42:48,128
We don't have the money.

624
00:42:48,212 --> 00:42:51,715
I can take some out of the deposit.

625
00:42:52,883 --> 00:42:54,968
The deposit is 200 million won.

626
00:42:55,052 --> 00:42:56,178
Hold on.

627
00:42:56,261 --> 00:42:58,180
Wait. No.

628
00:42:58,263 --> 00:42:59,223
Mom.

629
00:42:59,306 --> 00:43:01,809
I love my job right now.

630
00:43:04,645 --> 00:43:05,979
I-rang.

631
00:43:06,063 --> 00:43:06,980
Yes?

632
00:43:07,064 --> 00:43:09,400
You know I believe in you, right?

633
00:43:11,568 --> 00:43:13,404
Yes, I do.

634
00:43:13,487 --> 00:43:15,823
I'm not sure what's concerning you,

635
00:43:17,116 --> 00:43:18,534
but do what you want.

636
00:43:18,617 --> 00:43:20,160
I've got your back.

637
00:43:23,330 --> 00:43:25,374
Goodness, Mom.

638
00:43:26,333 --> 00:43:27,876
You're drunk after one glass of soju.

639
00:43:29,461 --> 00:43:31,714
Okay. Go to sleep now.

640
00:43:32,756 --> 00:43:33,632
I will.

641
00:43:34,174 --> 00:43:35,926
You should go to bed soon too.

642
00:43:36,009 --> 00:43:36,844
Okay.

643
00:44:06,957 --> 00:44:09,460
TAEBAEK LAW FIRM

644
00:44:10,377 --> 00:44:12,880
That's not very satisfying.

645
00:44:15,424 --> 00:44:17,593
Do you realize how much
I'm paying you guys?

646
00:44:18,510 --> 00:44:20,846
The bereaved must be
signing the agreement by now.

647
00:44:21,472 --> 00:44:22,389
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

648
00:44:22,473 --> 00:44:24,266
Ms. Kim, you're very lucky.

649
00:44:24,850 --> 00:44:27,936
The doctor didn't even kill your husband,

650
00:44:28,020 --> 00:44:31,190
but to take moral responsibility,
he's offering as much as 30 million won.

651
00:44:31,273 --> 00:44:33,776
The police investigation isn't over yet.

652
00:44:33,859 --> 00:44:34,985
And if it is over?

653
00:44:35,819 --> 00:44:36,695
Take it to court?

654
00:44:37,279 --> 00:44:39,323
- Yes, if needed.
- Goodness.

655
00:44:40,324 --> 00:44:42,534
Why would you want to complicate things?

656
00:44:43,577 --> 00:44:44,745
It's easier said than done.

657
00:44:44,828 --> 00:44:47,664
You don't know how tricky it is
to prove medical malpractice.

658
00:44:48,248 --> 00:44:50,751
If a single thing goes wrong,
you may even lose your house.

659
00:44:51,877 --> 00:44:54,129
I hear your daughter is sick.

660
00:44:54,213 --> 00:44:57,591
What if you end up on the street
with your sick daughter?

661
00:44:57,674 --> 00:44:58,759
Goodness.

662
00:44:58,842 --> 00:45:02,221
Attorney Han, tell me if I'm wrong.

663
00:45:04,848 --> 00:45:07,726
Your late husband's life
can't be measured by money,

664
00:45:07,809 --> 00:45:10,020
but please consider it
as a token of sincerity.

665
00:45:10,729 --> 00:45:13,315
Of course, the decision is up to you.

666
00:45:14,650 --> 00:45:16,068
Can I take a look at it?

667
00:45:16,151 --> 00:45:20,280
You may read it through
if you can't trust me,

668
00:45:20,364 --> 00:45:22,741
but would you be able to understand it?

669
00:45:24,451 --> 00:45:27,496
It's only natural for a settling party
to read through an agreement.

670
00:45:28,413 --> 00:45:29,665
Keep your manners.

671
00:45:31,250 --> 00:45:32,626
Actually, it's okay.

672
00:45:33,126 --> 00:45:34,795
I'm sure the attorney reviewed it well.

673
00:45:35,837 --> 00:45:38,215
Good thinking. Please sign there.

674
00:45:40,133 --> 00:45:42,469
KIM MIN…

675
00:45:44,429 --> 00:45:45,847
Excuse me for a moment.

676
00:45:49,726 --> 00:45:51,353
What are you doing here, Mr. Shin?

677
00:45:51,436 --> 00:45:52,854
You remember me.

678
00:45:52,938 --> 00:45:54,982
Are you Mr. Lee Jeong-seok's attorney?

679
00:45:58,694 --> 00:46:01,280
I hope I'm not too late.

680
00:46:01,363 --> 00:46:02,239
Excuse me.

681
00:46:03,115 --> 00:46:04,783
Oh, thank goodness.

682
00:46:04,866 --> 00:46:05,701
Wait.

683
00:46:05,784 --> 00:46:07,619
Do you know him?

684
00:46:08,662 --> 00:46:11,123
Who are you to--

685
00:46:11,206 --> 00:46:13,875
You can take time to learn about me

686
00:46:13,959 --> 00:46:16,086
because I'll say a few things
about you first.

687
00:46:16,837 --> 00:46:18,213
Attorney Byeon Seung-jun.

688
00:46:18,297 --> 00:46:20,966
Since graduating from the Judicial
Research and Training Institute in 2017,

689
00:46:21,049 --> 00:46:25,053
you worked at Taebaek
for five years and three months

690
00:46:25,137 --> 00:46:26,805
until July of 2022.

691
00:46:28,932 --> 00:46:31,351
Yes, what about it? Is there a problem?

692
00:46:31,977 --> 00:46:36,231
Taebaek is the dream law firm
that every attorney wants to work for.

693
00:46:36,315 --> 00:46:37,357
Yes, you're right.

694
00:46:37,441 --> 00:46:39,192
And this field is so small

695
00:46:39,276 --> 00:46:42,154
that you may be acquaintances
with the other party's attorney.

696
00:46:42,237 --> 00:46:45,198
That's honestly a little leery.

697
00:46:45,282 --> 00:46:46,158
So,

698
00:46:47,075 --> 00:46:48,619
what is your point?

699
00:46:48,702 --> 00:46:53,165
It turns out that Attorney Byeon
and Managing Partner Yang Do-gyeong

700
00:46:55,250 --> 00:46:56,918
played golf together last weekend

701
00:46:57,669 --> 00:46:59,296
and had a private talk afterward.

702
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:02,090
Hey, are you snooping on me?

703
00:47:02,174 --> 00:47:03,091
Me?

704
00:47:03,175 --> 00:47:04,926
Of course not.

705
00:47:11,433 --> 00:47:12,476
Oh, my goodness!

706
00:47:14,770 --> 00:47:16,188
Mr. Lee, congratulations.

707
00:47:17,814 --> 00:47:21,068
You won free legal service
at my office's grand opening event.

708
00:47:23,862 --> 00:47:24,988
Mr. Attorney.

709
00:47:26,156 --> 00:47:28,367
I'm quite smart, so you can count on me.

710
00:47:29,201 --> 00:47:30,077
Thank you.

711
00:47:31,828 --> 00:47:33,038
But what do we do?

712
00:47:33,121 --> 00:47:36,166
My wife already has an attorney.

713
00:47:36,249 --> 00:47:37,918
I looked into it

714
00:47:38,001 --> 00:47:39,795
and her attorney has many issues.

715
00:47:39,878 --> 00:47:42,422
He will definitely not defend your wife.

716
00:47:43,006 --> 00:47:43,882
Then, what do we do?

717
00:47:43,965 --> 00:47:45,258
Isn't it obvious?

718
00:47:45,342 --> 00:47:46,385
We'll have him fired.

719
00:47:47,719 --> 00:47:50,764
Like a ghost without letting anyone know.

720
00:47:59,314 --> 00:48:00,524
Excuse me.

721
00:48:01,191 --> 00:48:02,109
What are you doing?

722
00:48:02,192 --> 00:48:05,821
Wait just a moment.
The real deal is about to begin.

723
00:48:07,322 --> 00:48:08,740
Here it is.

724
00:48:08,824 --> 00:48:11,034
Hello, Mr. Yang. It's me.

725
00:48:11,118 --> 00:48:14,871
Attorneys always want
to leave advantageous evidence.

726
00:48:14,955 --> 00:48:17,124
You'll wire the money
to my borrowed-name account, right?

727
00:48:17,207 --> 00:48:18,500
Did you convince Kim Min-ju?

728
00:48:20,085 --> 00:48:22,254
It was extremely hard
to minimize the settlement money.

729
00:48:22,337 --> 00:48:23,171
I mean…

730
00:48:23,255 --> 00:48:24,548
…if not for me

731
00:48:25,173 --> 00:48:27,092
your client would've had to pay up
like a billion won.

732
00:48:28,677 --> 00:48:29,636
How could you!

733
00:48:30,262 --> 00:48:31,263
How…

734
00:48:31,346 --> 00:48:34,474
This is bad enough
to lose your law license.

735
00:48:35,142 --> 00:48:36,393
It's not good at all.

736
00:48:36,476 --> 00:48:38,520
Wait.

737
00:48:38,603 --> 00:48:41,106
I can explain. I can explain it all.

738
00:48:41,773 --> 00:48:44,192
Attorney Han, where are you going?
Attorney Han.

739
00:48:46,778 --> 00:48:49,698
Do I have any reason left to stay here?

740
00:49:00,292 --> 00:49:01,918
We don't need your explanation.

741
00:49:02,002 --> 00:49:04,463
Pull out of this case immediately.

742
00:49:04,546 --> 00:49:07,883
And wire twice the commission
you've received

743
00:49:07,966 --> 00:49:09,509
to Ms. Kim's account.

744
00:49:10,677 --> 00:49:11,803
Understand?

745
00:49:15,932 --> 00:49:16,975
Attorney Shin.

746
00:49:18,435 --> 00:49:19,519
Thank you.

747
00:49:24,232 --> 00:49:26,443
What are you going to do now?

748
00:49:27,194 --> 00:49:28,570
You will file a suit, right?

749
00:49:29,070 --> 00:49:31,573
If I file a suit and things go wrong…

750
00:49:33,366 --> 00:49:36,745
Why do you think your daughter is
locking herself up in her room?

751
00:49:38,455 --> 00:49:39,289
Excuse me?

752
00:49:39,372 --> 00:49:43,001
Maybe she's mad at the current situation.

753
00:49:44,503 --> 00:49:47,839
It's already devastating
that her dad died of a simple operation,

754
00:49:49,508 --> 00:49:50,967
but her mom is about to give up

755
00:49:51,885 --> 00:49:53,386
even without taking it to court.

756
00:50:00,936 --> 00:50:01,895
I…

757
00:50:03,021 --> 00:50:04,189
felt the same.

758
00:50:06,024 --> 00:50:07,859
She knows that

759
00:50:09,027 --> 00:50:11,863
her mom is suffering the most
from her dad's sudden death.

760
00:50:12,364 --> 00:50:14,324
How did the interview go?

761
00:50:17,285 --> 00:50:19,871
Well, I think I did a good job.

762
00:50:20,914 --> 00:50:22,833
She can't bring herself
to say such a thing.

763
00:50:25,544 --> 00:50:26,878
If I were you,

764
00:50:27,796 --> 00:50:29,756
I'd ask Ji-woo what she thinks.

765
00:50:44,563 --> 00:50:47,566
JI-WOO

766
00:50:55,615 --> 00:50:57,325
Look, Ji-woo.

767
00:51:02,497 --> 00:51:04,374
What happened to your dad…

768
00:51:08,628 --> 00:51:10,046
wasn't an accident.

769
00:51:11,965 --> 00:51:15,719
His doctor made a mistake
during the operation,

770
00:51:18,263 --> 00:51:20,515
and it killed your dad.

771
00:51:23,143 --> 00:51:24,269
I want

772
00:51:25,604 --> 00:51:28,565
to punish the doctor
for what he did to your dad.

773
00:51:31,192 --> 00:51:32,611
What do you think?

774
00:52:02,015 --> 00:52:02,974
Win.

775
00:52:07,312 --> 00:52:08,271
Ji-woo.

776
00:52:09,981 --> 00:52:10,982
What did you say?

777
00:52:13,652 --> 00:52:15,320
Win the trial.

778
00:52:22,369 --> 00:52:23,244
Okay.

779
00:52:24,079 --> 00:52:26,498
I'll make sure to win

780
00:52:27,082 --> 00:52:32,379
and punish all those
who caused your dad's death.

781
00:52:53,233 --> 00:52:54,567
KIM MIN-JU

782
00:52:58,321 --> 00:52:59,864
Shin I-rang speaking.

783
00:53:00,448 --> 00:53:01,783
I'll do it.

784
00:53:01,866 --> 00:53:05,537
I will fight for Gang-pung and Ji-woo.

785
00:53:07,539 --> 00:53:08,832
You made a good decision.

786
00:53:10,166 --> 00:53:11,084
I will

787
00:53:12,627 --> 00:53:14,337
do my best to help you.

788
00:53:37,944 --> 00:53:39,029
I was taken here,

789
00:53:39,112 --> 00:53:41,364
said goodbye to my family,

790
00:53:41,448 --> 00:53:42,532
and entered the ER.

791
00:53:43,241 --> 00:53:45,785
There were about five people inside…

792
00:53:47,495 --> 00:53:48,788
- Hello.
- How may I help you?

793
00:53:48,872 --> 00:53:50,165
May I take a quick look inside?

794
00:53:50,248 --> 00:53:51,875
- It won't take long.
- No.

795
00:53:51,958 --> 00:53:53,418
- Please leave.
- Wait.

796
00:53:53,501 --> 00:53:54,502
- Come on.
- Leave.

797
00:53:54,586 --> 00:53:56,504
- Wait, I…
- We'll walk you out.

798
00:53:58,548 --> 00:53:59,674
I'm not a weird person!

799
00:54:07,891 --> 00:54:10,852
CHEONGIL HOSPITAL

800
00:54:13,146 --> 00:54:14,647
This won't do.

801
00:54:15,190 --> 00:54:16,107
No.

802
00:54:18,943 --> 00:54:20,361
Hello.

803
00:54:20,445 --> 00:54:22,781
I'm an inspector
from the Korean Hospital Association.

804
00:54:23,364 --> 00:54:25,658
I'm here to conduct a status survey

805
00:54:25,742 --> 00:54:27,786
for better working conditions
of hospital workers.

806
00:54:27,869 --> 00:54:29,621
I see. Please come this way.

807
00:54:29,704 --> 00:54:30,663
Sure.

808
00:54:35,376 --> 00:54:39,005
We've received a report that labor rights
aren't protected at this hospital

809
00:54:39,089 --> 00:54:40,715
due to the recent lack of resources.

810
00:54:41,299 --> 00:54:44,385
I need a list of hiring and termination
for the last six months.

811
00:54:45,512 --> 00:54:46,346
Well, that's…

812
00:54:48,848 --> 00:54:52,018
From 2019 to 2024…

813
00:54:52,102 --> 00:54:53,978
DREAM PRIVATE DETECTIVE AGENCY

814
00:54:57,816 --> 00:54:59,359
ALARM

815
00:55:16,251 --> 00:55:18,169
PETITION

816
00:55:38,690 --> 00:55:41,359
- Congratulations on your first trial!
- Congratulations on your first trial!

817
00:55:42,819 --> 00:55:45,613
Congrats!

818
00:55:48,324 --> 00:55:50,076
You'll win for sure today. You can do it!

819
00:55:50,660 --> 00:55:52,453
Uncle, crush them all.

820
00:55:52,996 --> 00:55:55,039
Da-bong, watch your language.

821
00:56:04,507 --> 00:56:06,259
You look amazing, my son.

822
00:56:06,342 --> 00:56:07,385
Good luck.

823
00:56:07,468 --> 00:56:09,262
And watch your manners in court.

824
00:56:10,597 --> 00:56:12,974
Don't you worry. I'll do well.

825
00:56:15,727 --> 00:56:17,061
I'm running late. See you.

826
00:56:17,145 --> 00:56:19,772
- Gosh, okay. We should hurry too.
- Oh, okay.

827
00:56:19,856 --> 00:56:21,983
Where are you all going?

828
00:56:22,066 --> 00:56:23,234
Isn't it obvious?

829
00:56:23,318 --> 00:56:25,570
We're going
to watch your first trial live.

830
00:56:25,653 --> 00:56:27,906
How exciting!

831
00:56:27,989 --> 00:56:30,158
Not you, Da-bong.
You have to go to kindergarten.

832
00:56:31,117 --> 00:56:33,661
Go on. We'll drop her off and follow you.

833
00:56:33,745 --> 00:56:37,040
- Shall we?
- Good luck, Uncle.

834
00:56:42,170 --> 00:56:43,296
Watch it live?

835
00:56:44,214 --> 00:56:45,965
This isn't the Premier League.

836
00:56:46,883 --> 00:56:49,385
COURT OF KOREA

837
00:56:52,222 --> 00:56:54,224
PLAINTIFF'S TABLE

838
00:57:01,648 --> 00:57:04,150
Don't worry. It will go well.

839
00:57:04,734 --> 00:57:05,652
Okay.

840
00:57:24,504 --> 00:57:25,588
I-rang.

841
00:57:30,927 --> 00:57:33,054
I already have enough to worry about.

842
00:57:42,438 --> 00:57:44,440
COURT OF KOREA

843
00:57:47,569 --> 00:57:49,320
You better wait here, Gang-pung.

844
00:57:49,404 --> 00:57:51,656
I can't afford to have you get worked up
during the trial.

845
00:57:54,867 --> 00:57:57,453
I move to examine the defendant,
Lee Jeong-seok, himself.

846
00:57:58,162 --> 00:57:59,080
Accepted.

847
00:57:59,747 --> 00:58:01,833
Defendant, come forward
to the witness stand.

848
00:58:09,841 --> 00:58:11,217
Oh, my goodness.

849
00:58:12,093 --> 00:58:14,053
Why did you come?
I told you to wait outside.

850
00:58:14,762 --> 00:58:16,889
Attorney Shin, are you okay?

851
00:58:16,973 --> 00:58:18,057
I solemnly swear…

852
00:58:18,141 --> 00:58:20,268
- My neck was itchy.
- …to speak the truth

853
00:58:20,351 --> 00:58:22,895
the whole truth and nothing but the truth,

854
00:58:23,521 --> 00:58:26,858
- and if I tell a lie…
- I remembered something I didn't tell you.

855
00:58:27,442 --> 00:58:28,568
Save it. I'm busy right now.

856
00:58:28,651 --> 00:58:30,236
I think it's important.

857
00:58:32,905 --> 00:58:34,073
That punk…

858
00:58:38,661 --> 00:58:40,079
That piece of trash.

859
00:58:40,163 --> 00:58:41,706
Don't get worked up.

860
00:58:42,749 --> 00:58:45,376
Defendant, you performed surgery
on Mr. Lee Gang-pung

861
00:58:45,460 --> 00:58:47,295
on October 13 last year, correct?

862
00:58:48,046 --> 00:58:49,255
Yes.

863
00:58:49,339 --> 00:58:52,133
Will you elaborate
on the situation at that time?

864
00:58:52,884 --> 00:58:54,927
Surgery for snoring is an easy operation.

865
00:58:55,762 --> 00:58:57,805
There was nothing unusual.

866
00:58:59,641 --> 00:59:01,559
According to the materials
from the hospital,

867
00:59:01,643 --> 00:59:05,396
Mr. Lee's case required a change
in the structure of his airway.

868
00:59:05,480 --> 00:59:07,398
Thus, general anesthesia was mandatory.

869
00:59:07,482 --> 00:59:08,316
That's right.

870
00:59:08,399 --> 00:59:10,652
But the problem was

871
00:59:10,735 --> 00:59:11,986
the patient's heart.

872
00:59:13,446 --> 00:59:14,864
That little…

873
00:59:14,947 --> 00:59:16,699
He's lying. It's all a lie!

874
00:59:16,783 --> 00:59:18,242
Calm down. No one else can hear you.

875
00:59:18,326 --> 00:59:19,577
I got this.

876
00:59:23,247 --> 00:59:24,207
That's all.

877
00:59:24,999 --> 00:59:27,418
Your cross, Counsel.

878
00:59:30,922 --> 00:59:32,006
Mr. Lee.

879
00:59:32,674 --> 00:59:35,718
How many nurses were present
during the operation?

880
00:59:38,096 --> 00:59:38,971
Two.

881
00:59:39,055 --> 00:59:41,474
Come on. You're lying.

882
00:59:41,974 --> 00:59:44,519
There were about five people inside.

883
00:59:44,602 --> 00:59:46,771
And three nurses.

884
00:59:50,149 --> 00:59:52,819
Aside from Kim Mi-yeong and Choi Ji-a
whom you reported to court,

885
00:59:55,029 --> 00:59:56,906
there was Oh Jin-suk.

886
00:59:57,657 --> 00:59:58,700
Pardon?

887
00:59:58,783 --> 00:59:59,867
Oh Jin-suk?

888
01:00:01,577 --> 01:00:04,372
Well… I don't know who that is.

889
01:00:04,455 --> 01:00:07,041
She was with you in the ER
until the very end.

890
01:00:07,834 --> 01:00:08,960
Good work, everyone.

891
01:00:09,043 --> 01:00:11,045
- Good work.
- Good work.

892
01:00:11,129 --> 01:00:13,464
She is the witness
who watched what happened

893
01:00:14,048 --> 01:00:15,049
at the closest.

894
01:00:18,761 --> 01:00:20,221
Sir, can you hear me?

895
01:00:20,304 --> 01:00:22,473
Sir? Sir.

896
01:00:23,641 --> 01:00:26,102
Darn, what's going on?

897
01:00:27,061 --> 01:00:29,605
His airway is blocked.
You must perform emergency surgery now!

898
01:00:31,274 --> 01:00:32,900
Should we prepare for a tracheostomy?

899
01:00:33,818 --> 01:00:35,445
- Doctor!
- Shut up!

900
01:00:35,528 --> 01:00:37,071
I'll handle it, okay?

901
01:00:44,829 --> 01:00:46,998
In case your crime got exposed,

902
01:00:47,790 --> 01:00:49,000
you hid the only witness,

903
01:00:50,001 --> 01:00:51,544
Oh Jin-suk, out of fear.

904
01:00:56,257 --> 01:00:58,092
I object, Your Honor.

905
01:00:59,093 --> 01:01:00,928
Let us hear more first.

906
01:01:01,512 --> 01:01:04,223
Counsel, you made
a crucial remark just now.

907
01:01:04,307 --> 01:01:08,561
Can we hear from Oh Jin-suk,
whom you claim to be a witness?

908
01:01:10,313 --> 01:01:11,397
It is

909
01:01:11,981 --> 01:01:13,691
not possible at the moment.

910
01:01:14,984 --> 01:01:19,155
The plaintiff's counsel is straying
from the point with unverified claims.

911
01:01:19,238 --> 01:01:22,450
Please consider
that his statement is inappropriate.

912
01:01:22,533 --> 01:01:23,701
Objection sustained.

913
01:01:24,243 --> 01:01:26,204
Counsel, speak your words carefully.

914
01:01:26,788 --> 01:01:27,747
Yes, Your Honor.

915
01:01:28,414 --> 01:01:29,540
Then today,

916
01:01:30,792 --> 01:01:33,961
I'd like to submit
just his facial expression as evidence.

917
01:01:34,754 --> 01:01:37,048
A facial expression cannot be evidence.

918
01:01:49,644 --> 01:01:50,603
That is all.

919
01:02:12,124 --> 01:02:12,959
Defendant.

920
01:02:13,960 --> 01:02:15,545
Does this kind of accident happen often?

921
01:02:16,295 --> 01:02:18,923
No, it's a rare case.

922
01:02:19,006 --> 01:02:21,801
Then, you must've wondered
what caused the accident.

923
01:02:23,511 --> 01:02:24,595
The thing is…

924
01:02:26,347 --> 01:02:29,183
If it's hard to speak,
should I talk on your behalf?

925
01:02:29,976 --> 01:02:30,977
Sure.

926
01:02:32,228 --> 01:02:34,730
The truth is, Lee Gang-pung was…

927
01:02:36,232 --> 01:02:37,650
a gangster.

928
01:02:38,609 --> 01:02:39,986
- What?
- A gangster?

929
01:02:40,069 --> 01:02:40,987
No way!

930
01:02:41,070 --> 01:02:42,989
- Really?
- Oh, my goodness.

931
01:02:45,908 --> 01:02:47,326
What is she saying?

932
01:02:47,410 --> 01:02:48,911
Gang-pung was a taxi driver.

933
01:02:50,246 --> 01:02:51,163
Your Honor.

934
01:02:51,664 --> 01:02:55,167
The defendant's counsel is
making up a story in this sacred court.

935
01:02:55,251 --> 01:02:56,127
I doubt that.

936
01:02:59,589 --> 01:03:02,049
Lee Gang-pung was part of the Oseong Gang

937
01:03:02,133 --> 01:03:03,759
- in Daejeon 20 years ago.
- Hello, sir!

938
01:03:05,177 --> 01:03:06,554
He has a prior assault conviction.

939
01:03:07,763 --> 01:03:09,599
And please look at his surgery scar here.

940
01:03:09,682 --> 01:03:11,976
He got stabbed in the right chest
at that time.

941
01:03:12,560 --> 01:03:14,770
A patient with the record
of a cardiac operation

942
01:03:14,854 --> 01:03:17,231
died of a cardiac attack
during his surgery.

943
01:03:17,815 --> 01:03:19,108
Is it really irrelevant?

944
01:03:26,449 --> 01:03:27,658
We're screwed.

945
01:03:30,119 --> 01:03:31,329
Your Honor.

946
01:03:31,412 --> 01:03:34,248
The defendant's counsel is
insulting the deceased

947
01:03:34,332 --> 01:03:36,167
as well as inciting hatred

948
01:03:36,250 --> 01:03:39,045
by showing unnecessary pictures
and overly bringing up his past.

949
01:03:39,128 --> 01:03:40,338
Sustained.

950
01:03:40,421 --> 01:03:42,298
Defendant's counsel, please watch it.

951
01:03:42,381 --> 01:03:45,384
I wouldn't have brought up his past

952
01:03:45,468 --> 01:03:48,054
if his behavior had only been in the past.

953
01:03:48,638 --> 01:03:52,099
But he caused a stir with violent words
and uncooperative actions

954
01:03:52,183 --> 01:03:54,226
during his hospitalization.

955
01:03:54,894 --> 01:03:55,895
That's a lie.

956
01:03:55,978 --> 01:03:58,981
Please tell us how he behaved
at the hospital.

957
01:03:59,941 --> 01:04:01,108
Patient Lee Gang-pung…

958
01:04:05,404 --> 01:04:06,781
spoke profanity all the time.

959
01:04:07,907 --> 01:04:10,660
He often scared the nurses
with intimidating behavior.

960
01:04:11,327 --> 01:04:14,330
I heard he did the same to his family.

961
01:04:19,085 --> 01:04:20,002
No.

962
01:04:23,714 --> 01:04:24,632
It's not true.

963
01:04:32,390 --> 01:04:34,725
This can't happen here.

964
01:04:34,809 --> 01:04:36,102
Oh, there's one more thing.

965
01:04:37,103 --> 01:04:38,980
I heard he abused
his middle school daughter.

966
01:04:39,814 --> 01:04:43,109
It caused her to have anorexia
and she's cooping herself up in her room.

967
01:04:43,901 --> 01:04:45,361
Being possessed

968
01:04:45,444 --> 01:04:48,322
manifests when their desires reach a peak.

969
01:04:48,990 --> 01:04:50,992
When they're faced with someone they hate

970
01:04:51,075 --> 01:04:53,119
or something that causes rage,

971
01:04:53,911 --> 01:04:56,330
the possibility of possession increases.

972
01:04:57,581 --> 01:04:58,582
Hey, punk.

973
01:04:59,166 --> 01:05:01,585
Are you out of your goddamn mind?

974
01:05:02,169 --> 01:05:05,715
You're running your mouth
because you see nothing, aren't you?

975
01:05:06,257 --> 01:05:07,842
Are those eyes for show?

976
01:05:07,925 --> 01:05:10,511
Then, give 'em to me instead.

977
01:05:11,137 --> 01:05:14,890
Goodness, this reminds me of the ol' days.

978
01:05:15,433 --> 01:05:17,101
I have quite a lot of experience

979
01:05:17,184 --> 01:05:18,352
in prison.

980
01:05:18,436 --> 01:05:22,064
What is he saying?
And what's wrong with his cheeks?

981
01:05:22,148 --> 01:05:24,150
Mom, I'm getting a feeling

982
01:05:24,233 --> 01:05:25,568
that something bad will happen.

983
01:05:26,944 --> 01:05:29,280
Plaintiff's counsel, go back to your seat.

984
01:05:29,363 --> 01:05:31,323
Dang it, why should I sit down?

985
01:05:31,407 --> 01:05:33,451
That man should be the one sitting

986
01:05:33,534 --> 01:05:34,535
in his coffin.

987
01:05:34,618 --> 01:05:39,707
Punk, how dare you mess around
with your pathetic lies?

988
01:05:39,790 --> 01:05:42,209
You and that little mouth of yours.
I should just…

989
01:06:30,299 --> 01:06:31,759
I truly hate

990
01:06:33,219 --> 01:06:34,804
being a ghost-seeing attorney.

991
01:07:07,878 --> 01:07:09,630
This happened because I was such a softie.

992
01:07:09,713 --> 01:07:11,632
No! Not now!

993
01:07:11,715 --> 01:07:13,926
Don't try to get in the way,
or I'll make you pay.

994
01:07:14,009 --> 01:07:15,719
They submitted
a fabricated record to court.

995
01:07:15,803 --> 01:07:16,846
Search through the EMR.

996
01:07:16,929 --> 01:07:19,557
Consider yourself blessed
to have Attorney Han defend you.

997
01:07:19,640 --> 01:07:21,725
Han Na-hyun would even risk her life
to win a trial.

998
01:07:21,809 --> 01:07:23,310
I'm from the Prosecutors' Office.

999
01:07:23,394 --> 01:07:25,271
I don't care if she's a prosecutor.
Get her.

1000
01:07:30,151 --> 01:07:31,527
- Who are you?
- Me?

1001
01:07:34,113 --> 01:07:36,949
I'm a gangster attorney, Lee Gang-pung!

1002
01:07:37,908 --> 01:07:42,913
Subtitle translation by:
Eunjin Erica Kim
